text: Sugarcane tasted diluted. Ordered one regular and one large - both were of the same quality. Not sure if the store was closing and didn't have enough but it is the worst sugarcane juice that I have ever tasted. Bought another cup from a different store nearby to confirm it was not due to a bad sugarcane season. The intensity of the colour between the 2 cups were totally different.

Would have loved to get my sugarcane juice from them, but they've already ran out around 745pm on a Sunday evening. At the very least, the stall owners were kind enough to come apologize and be nice about the situation, which I thoroughly appreciate. I just said "awww it's alright next time then thanks", and walked off.
Have patronise this store for many years and the sugar cane is one of the best among the rest. Their sugarcane is not diluted and is really value for money.
